sec.p:
Two high-PAS sessions were scheduled in a randomized order. In one session, 20-min high-PAS was targeted such that the arrival of the TMS and PNS pulses was estimated to occur spinally (SPINAL) and another cortically (CORTICAL). A single high-intensity TMS pulse was timed with predetermined ISI to coincide with the first pulse of the PNS train applied from the peripheral nerve trunk via electrical stimulation such that the arriving pulses coincide at the desired level, either spinally or cortically. High-PAS ISIs were adjusted individually for every subject and session. To precisely target the pulses arrival to the spinal-cord level, the required ISI was computed using the formula \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
